Package: nilHMM
Title: Duration-Aware HMM Ancestry Caller for NIL Sequencing Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Fausto", "Rodriguez Zapata", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "thegemmalab@ncsu.edu")
Description: A unified R + Rcpp reimplementation of the nilHMM ancestry-calling
    family for Near-Isogenic Lines from sequencing data. A single
    duration-aware 3-state (REF/HET/ALT) HMM engine with swappable emission
    models (count / gt / dosage) and duration layers (geometric / rigidity /
    hsmm) expresses the nnil, rtiger and skimbin callers. The package is
    data-agnostic: functions take (data, params) and return calls; pipeline
    scripts own paths and sample lists. See REFACTOR_R_PACKAGE.md.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1)
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    GenomicRanges
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
